  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve macroeconomic stability in Ghana by strengthening the inflation targeting framework, building the capacity of the central bank to manage financial crisis, and developing the regulatory framework of the Securities and Exchange Commission.  This will reduce inflation, bank lending rates, and non-performing loans and improve Ghana&#x2019;s credit rating.    These interventions will contribute toward SDG 8 (Promote sustained, inclusive and sustainable economic growth, full and productive employment and decent work for all) and 16 (Promote peaceful and inclusive societies for sustainable development, provide access to justice for all and build effective, accountable and inclusive institutions at all levels)</narrative>
  </description>
